  note = {Remarkably, cadherin adhesions are not passive tethers; they are mechanosensitive. Tension exerted on E-cadherin junctions can induce molecular changes -- for example, stretching of {$\alpha$}-catenin under force increases its affinity for vinculin, strengthening the actin link
\par
their intracellular tails connect via catenin proteins to the actin cytoskeleton. In this way, adherens junctions couple the force-generating actomyosin networks of neighboring cells, allowing one cell's contractile forces to be conveyed to its neighbors},
